plyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2388.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   New Ragefire...bleh</span><hr size=1> M'kay...<br><br>After what happened with Ragefire yesterday, well, I just wanted to get some feedback from the rest of the server as to whether VI has screwed us as badly as I think they have.<br><br>Basically, it seems to me that the new Ragefire camp has become Sev2.  Except that you can't predict reliably when the spawn will occur, like with Sev.  Yesterday, one of Unconquered's clerics had a monk FD at the spawn location of the new Ragefire in Skyfire (a cleric who has everything else he needs for his epic, yes).  Basically the whole guild had been helping watching for the spawn, as many of us tried to keep a FD monk or a tracker in the area to help with the camp effort over the last few weeks.  Sorta like it was SolB.  <br><br>Anyway, Rage spawns, we begin mobilizing (but not as fast as we possibly could have, since I guess we felt we had the spawn and had no real rush to zergling rush the entire guild there).  Nobody thought to kite Zord (I guess cause we had a monk FD at his feet), AA gets there while we are mobilizing and kites him until the rest of their troops arrive and later kills him. <br><br>As far as how Unconquered feels about this...<br><br>1) We are disappointed Stumpp was not able to complete his epic, seeing that he had &quot;camped&quot; the spawn in the old style of Ragefire camping which was, as we had observed by the respect people demonstrated in SolB, a valid way to camp it when Ragefire was in SolB.<br><br>2) We were sincerely hoping that, due to the multi-day window in which this mob can spawn, the same etiquette that was extended to clerics camping it in SolB would be extended to clerics camping it in Skyfire.<br><br>3) We do not feel AA did anything wrong. We are aware and we certainly could have kited Zord around, we just did not expect it to come to that.<br><br>4) We congradulate AA on their kill and their new epic cleric. We are worried and disappointed that their actions may turn a spawn which was handled with a good degree of etiquette on Drinal (when it was in SolB) into another Severilous, which is one of the most disgusting fought over spawns on Drinal. <br><br>What I'm really trying to say is....do we have to turn Rage into Sev2?  Sev sucks.  We all know Sev sucks.  At least with Sev, you know when its gonna pop.  With Rage you have a 50 hour window, at least, according what I have seen so far on eqclerics.  I guess we were assuming the same respect for a cleric camping the spawn that was shown to clerics in SolB would be shown to clerics in Skyfire.  I don't know why Drinal hadn't had the same kind of problems other servers had with Ragefire in SolB, but honestly, I have been a part of many Ragefire camps over the last few months and people were very respectful of that camp effort in SolB, whether it was just a FD monk, a group clearing FG's, or whatever, people respected it.  <br><br>Just wanted to get some discussion going.  I am now of the opinion that we'll just have to handle this like Sev, and basically, when Rage pops, you can get your force there fastest and get &quot;initial agro&quot; by kiting him until your troops arrive.  Zeny has been trying to hammer the point into me that we don't have a choice, VI turned it into Sev2, but I am of the opinion that the Sev spawn stinks to high heaven and I can't see why we want that again.  Unfortunately...rare epic spawn...outdoor zone...easily accessable to druid/wizard portals...well, you get the point.  It's going to become another Sev.<br><br>Kudos to AA for getting the kill, and to whichever cleric is the lucky holder of a new water sprinker.  I have no hard feelings, and I chalk this up as us just struggling together to set the &quot;rules&quot; for how this spawn is going to work on Drinal.  <br><br>Seke<br>Unconquered<br><br>*edit fixed typos* <p></p