ait it out due to RL issues or even fatigue.  Then when sev would spawn the next day, that person felt they had as legitimate a claim, based on time invested, as the person who was currently camping the spawn.  It went downhill from there.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/utrewayn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trewayn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=red><B>Dranalite<B></FONT></span><br>  Posts: 186<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 8:43:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2388.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New Ragefire...bleh</span><hr size=1> IMO This is not going to be another Sev spawn.  This is going to be a whole lot worse.  The warrior epics are nice to have but are one of the first epics to be made obsolete by other items now dropping in the game.  The same cannot be said for the cleric epic.  It was, is and always will be the most important epic to any high level guild which does any degree of raiding.<br><br>I think one of the reasons the SolB camp has remained so civil is the effective &quot;remoteness&quot; of the area.  It's in the far end of a zone and actually required some small degree of effort to monitor (i.e. killing giants to get the area and possibly keeping them cleared.)  Nobody is about to battle their way through a semi-spawn of giants just to bicker with a camper over a spawn.  New Rage is so easy to get to that this effectively cheapens his rareness by increasing his accessibility.  Add to this the very real danger that some guilds may even kill him just to farm for warrior and bard scales and you end up with a nightmare for clerics.<br><br>It's been proved time and again that trying to organise some kind of etiquette on Sev doesn't work.  It would be great if something could be worked out on one spawn or the other and applied to both, but I don't hold out much hope that it will.<br><br>Are there any threads on the cleric forums regarding this problem? <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24811">Trewayn Fifate</A>, <font size=1><EM>Virtuoso, master artisan and all round good egg</EM><br><a href="http://nmcs.com/kingscourt"><b>King's Court</b></a>, <a href="http://www.drinal.com">Drinal</a><p><table border=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=40%><tr><td width=15%></td><td width=10%><td width=15%></td><td width=10%><td width=15%></td><td width=10%></tr><tr><td><b>Tailoring</b></td><td><b>210</b></td><td>Fishing</td><td>198</td><td>Pottery</td><td>169</td></tr><tr><td>Baking</td><td>157</td><td>Smithing</td><td>135</td><td>Fletching</td><td>181</td></tr><tr><td>Brewing</td><td>187</td><td>Jewelry</td><td>170</td><td>Drunkard</td><td>200</td></tr></table></br></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/useke2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>seke2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=red><B>Dranalite<B></FONT></span><br>  Posts: 159<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/7/02 8:48:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2388.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New Ragefire...bleh</span><hr size=1> I don't really think the events of yesterday are relevant to the discussion.  I'll answer your questions, Asanti, but I don't see the relevance to the overall discussion.  I've talked with AA's leaders, so have my other officers, and there doesn't seem to be any unresolved issues.<br><br>I got all this info second hand since I hadn't logged on yet, so perhaps one of my guildies who was online when this happened can give more specifics, but as far as I know:  <b