ubject I, personally, still have no real good ideas on this.<br><br>I am, of course happy for Iyena, a the priestess in our guild who did get the heart.<br><br>From a different perspective though, I know that Winnette, an officer, and epic holding priestess in our guild along with a number of others had done some discussions on camping Rage.  Unconquered from the beginning was seeing the new rage as a camp just like the old one.  From a post i went back and looked at on our boards, from the beginning we were looking at him as a Sev camp, one of the reasons we never bothered posting the famous sleeping monk, like we've done in the past.  We have had druids (Qtea, Casidy, and a few others) make regular passes between there and EJ to look for him on track (it wasn't an accident that he was spotted so quickly by one of our druids).<br><br>What the end product was:  2 guilds who had camped a mob in 2 completely different ways under different assumptions.<br><br>Frankly i don't like either of the options:<br>With doing it the old style, what ends up happening?   a monk is sitting there and as soon as one rage goes down FD's, and claims next spawn?  What happens when 2 3 or 4 guilds have monks there just waiting to FD?  It's not like the old style where there may be a naggy there between em, or you have to work through FG's and a zone of annoying greens to get to the spot to lay the claim.<br><br>With the option we used.....ick.  I've never liked the PNP rules as they are.  I despise the sev camp and all that it's about, and this one (even if we did &quot;win&quot;-a term i lightly use-) is no exception.  We have adapted to them, and do work by them, they are the rules weather we like them or not.<br><br>AA a few months ago came to fully embrace the PNP rules a few months ago, not out of like for them, but out of need.  On several raids we lost out on because we tried to do the &quot;nice&quot; thing and let those who were gathering first go ahead, then we were loosing out because we were starting a raid first and someone else mobilized faster than we did.  Basically we were loosing out all around from trying to work with the &quot;honor&quot; system.  It came down to either loosing out all around, or embracing the system that goes by the rules.<br><br>With this new spawn, it's a bit worse than Sev........   just aggroing sev and leading him around the zone on a leash is not the easiest of tasks LOL.   Rage in human form however is pretty easy.  So, just like the group of FDing monks stated above, It can turn into the group of bards/druids/rangers just standing by the spawn hoping to grab his attention first.  THEN i see more arguements popping about who has forces to take him down first after all, it isn't JUST about aggro but who can do it as well............  I forsee many more ugly situations comming out of this, a lot of grief and heartache.  Hope i'm wrong, but i don't think so.<br><br>With Respect and Regards;<br>Astpahs Vorn`Sharrek<br>55th circle Beguiler of Erudin<br>Member of Arcane Asylum <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showMessageRange?topicID=2388.topic&start=21&stop=31>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=2388.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showNextMessage?topicID=2388.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2388.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/fr/themes/default/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.threadControl?topicID=2388.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/fr/themes/defa